through mediation today.

00:45:15.507 --> 00:45:17.259
Yes, I'll do that.

00:45:22.431 --> 00:45:24.641
Did you really regret it?

00:45:27.561 --> 00:45:30.647
Do you really understand how painful

00:45:31.523 --> 00:45:32.524
this is for us?

00:45:36.653 --> 00:45:39.156
We sincerely hope this can be resolved,

00:45:39.656 --> 00:45:43.702
so both of you can move on
and start anew...

00:45:43.785 --> 00:45:45.120
Move on?

00:45:47.247 --> 00:45:50.209
Peacefully without causing further harm?

00:45:52.711 --> 00:45:54.129
You think that's possible?

00:45:54.213 --> 00:45:56.548
Do you think settling with him

00:45:57.758 --> 00:45:59.009
will fix everything?

00:46:02.012 --> 00:46:03.055
Geez.

00:46:04.556 --> 00:46:05.599
If I had just

00:46:06.767 --> 00:46:08.727
given up my inheritance,

00:46:09.770 --> 00:46:12.856
I wouldn't have had to go through
the ordeal of paying damages

00:46:13.357 --> 00:46:15.108
to my husband's mistress.

00:46:18.195 --> 00:46:20.531
But I have two kids to feed.

00:46:22.282 --> 00:46:26.745
And we need that house
under Song Yeongcheol's name to survive.

00:46:29.164 --> 00:46:30.165
I was…

00:46:30.791 --> 00:46:33.335
So pathetic
that I couldn't give up my inheritance.

00:46:35.087 --> 00:46:38.590
You have no idea how it feels
to suffer this humiliation.

00:46:43.470 --> 00:46:46.431
That's why instead of leaving it
to the court,

00:46:46.515 --> 00:46:49.351
we brought both parties here
to settle it themselves.

00:46:49.434 --> 00:46:50.853
So please try to stay calm.

00:46:50.936 --> 00:46:52.396
Are you saying

00:46:52.896 --> 00:46:55.899
if I handle things myself and settle,
I'll get a fresh start?

00:46:57.067 --> 00:47:00.445
Do you think he feels at peace right now?

00:47:09.329 --> 00:47:10.664
I mean,

00:47:12.624 --> 00:47:14.585
if this were something I did,

00:47:16.587 --> 00:47:19.464
I'd take full responsibility.

00:47:20.257 --> 00:47:25.012
But I didn't do any of this!

00:47:34.229 --> 00:47:35.647
There's no way

00:47:36.982 --> 00:47:38.275
that I can personally

00:47:39.234 --> 00:47:42.571
hand over the money
to my husband's mistress.

00:47:42.654 --> 00:47:44.615
So please, just give a verdict.

00:47:44.698 --> 00:47:47.034
Just take it from me by force.

00:47:47.117 --> 00:47:51.205
I absolutely cannot bring myself
to personally pay them.

00:48:11.225 --> 00:48:12.684
This is driving me crazy.

00:48:13.810 --> 00:48:17.981
DEFENDANT PARK SUJEONG

00:48:27.491 --> 00:48:29.910
This will confirm
that the divorce finalized

00:48:29.993 --> 00:48:31.995
and there are no remaining claims

00:48:32.079 --> 00:48:35.332
for anything owed,
such as alimony or asset division.

00:48:35.874 --> 00:48:41.463
COUNSEL AHN JUHYEONG

00:49:06.655 --> 00:49:08.532
- Are you okay?
- Yes, I'm fine.

00:49:09.032 --> 00:49:11.952
So in this case,
there likely will be one more trial date.

00:49:12.035 --> 00:49:14.830
If things wrap up then,
they'll set the date for the verdict.

00:49:15.664 --> 00:49:17.165
Yes, I understand.

00:49:20.335 --> 00:49:23.213
Excuse me. Thank you for your time.

00:49:28.135 --> 00:49:29.803
Does someone like you

00:49:30.679 --> 00:49:33.056
even understand how someone like me feels?

00:49:34.933 --> 00:49:36.018
Let's go now.

00:49:37.519 --> 00:49:39.479
People like you
are born into nice families

00:49:39.563 --> 00:49:41.732
and go to expensive law schools,

00:49:41.815 --> 00:49:44.526
where it's easier
to become a lawyer.

00:49:45.152 --> 00:49:47.404
How could you even relate
to something like this?

00:49:48.322 --> 00:49:49.948
You named my kids as defendants!

00:49:51.825 --> 00:49:55.120
You shouldn't live your life like that.

00:49:55.954 --> 00:49:56.997
Let's go.

00:49:59.291 --> 00:50:02.002
I looked you up to see
what kind of person you were.

00:50:02.085 --> 00:50:04.213
You're not the only one
who looked into things!

00:50:10.219 --> 00:50:12.221
- Attorney Ha.
- Yes?

00:50:12.304 --> 00:50:15.057
- Let's just go.
- Yes, let's go.

00:50:39.373 --> 00:50:42.417
The case ended in your favor,
so you won't need to come in anymore.

00:50:43.919 --> 00:50:48.215
How could I not show up
after hearing such good news?

00:50:55.347 --> 00:50:57.391
It's nothing much.
Just a gift certificate.

00:50:57.474 --> 00:50:59.268
I wanted to show my thanks.

00:51:00.394 --> 00:51:02.688
- So please take it.
- No, it's okay.

00:51:03.981 --> 00:51:04.982
Come on.

00:51:05.899 --> 00:51:07.651
Take it!

00:51:09.027 --> 00:51:12.322
You pulled off a clean win.

00:51:16.243 --> 00:51:18.287
Yes, thank you.

00:51:24.459 --> 00:51:28.380
I'm so glad I had you take the case.

00:51:31.592 --> 00:51:32.843
I made

00:51:33.677 --> 00:51:36.763
a specific request
when I talked to Mr. Na.

00:51:37.723 --> 00:51:41.810
I asked for you
to be put on my case.

00:51:43.145 --> 00:51:44.563
- Me?
- Yes.

00:51:44.646 --> 00:51:46.690
You, Attorney Ahn Juhyeong.

00:51:57.951 --> 00:52:02.748
I figured if she had to deal with her ex,
it would make her uncomfortable.

00:52:03.790 --> 00:52:05.125
It looks like I was right.

00:52:10.339 --> 00:52:11.757
You look very surprised.

00:52:12.549 --> 00:52:13.592
I see.

00:52:15.844 --> 00:52:18.305
- You came to me on purpose?
- Yes.

00:52:18.388 --> 00:52:20.891
I came here on purpose to buy you.

00:52:23.143 --> 00:52:25.270
We're getting divorced anyway.

00:52:25.354 --> 00:52:28.357
What's the point of being polite?
It does no good for me.

00:52:28.440 --> 00:52:29.858
How did you find out about me?

00:52:31.151 --> 00:52:32.152
What?

00:52:33.028 --> 00:52:34.571
Afraid Sujeong talked about you?

00:52:34.655 --> 00:52:36.281
How did you find out?

00:52:41.203 --> 00:52:42.329
Remember Jung Jihun?

00:52:43.288 --> 00:52:44.456
Sujeong's friend?

00:52:45.040 --> 00:52:47.125
He's always been a nuisance.

00:52:47.960 --> 00:52:50.420
He's foolish and doesn't have
a filter when he talks.

00:52:52.548 --> 00:52:55.843
He once got drunk in front of me
and started talking about you.

00:52:57.845 --> 00:52:58.887
You don't know him?

00:52:59.471 --> 00:53:00.639
Not really.

00:53:00.722 --> 00:53:02.099
It doesn't ring a bell.

00:53:06.687 --> 00:53:07.688
Really?

00:53:08.522 --> 00:53:09.523
Then,

00:53:10.566 --> 00:53:13.193
that's all the more reason to take this.

00:53:13.819 --> 00:53:14.862
Here.

00:53:16.154 --> 00:53:17.155
Good work.

00:53:18.198 --> 00:53:19.199
Enjoy it.

00:53:20.075 --> 00:53:22.035
Buy yourself something nice.

00:53:23.287 --> 00:53:25.080
DIVORCE
CHA JEONGHO, PARK SUJEONG

00:53:25.163 --> 00:53:28.125
SETTLEMENT REACHED

00:53:29.418 --> 00:53:30.961
It looks like they settled.

00:53:31.503 --> 00:53:32.629
DEFENDANT PARK SUJEONG

00:53:32.713 --> 00:53:36.884
LAW GROUP HYUNGMIN
ATTORNEY IN CHARGE: AHN JUHYEONG

00:53:55.777 --> 00:53:57.237
AHN JUHYEONG

00:53:57.321 --> 00:53:59.948
THANKS FOR TODAY
I'll TREAT YOU NEXT TIME

00:54:00.032 --> 00:54:02.367
OKAY, GOOD NIGHT

00:54:07.998 --> 00:54:11.835
ARE YOU OKAY?

00:54:41.907 --> 00:54:43.325
I didn't think it would rip.

00:54:43.992 --> 00:54:45.452
I guess you didn't put in much.

00:54:47.496 --> 00:54:48.580
Thank you for the gift.

00:54:56.129 --> 00:54:58.966
I can't believe there's someone
who would turn down cash.

00:55:00.217 --> 00:55:03.053
It was probably worth
as much as your monthly salary.

00:55:03.637 --> 00:55:06.557
Says the guy who sought me out
just to save 10 million won.

00:55:07.599 --> 00:55:11.478
Geez, how am I supposed buy a lawyer
if you make me feel so self-conscious?

00:55:12.896 --> 00:55:13.939
I paid

00:55:14.857 --> 00:55:17.317
with my money to buy you.

00:55:17.985 --> 00:55:19.027
Don't forget that.

00:55:19.111 --> 00:55:22.155
If it weren't for that,
I wouldn't bother with trash like you.

00:55:23.365 --> 00:55:26.410
Since that's over, just quietly get lost.

00:55:26.493 --> 00:55:27.744
You little…

00:55:27.828 --> 00:55:29.580
Hey.

00:55:30.330 --> 00:55:31.582
Hey, you…

00:55:34.751 --> 00:55:36.670
We would have evidence here this time.

00:55:38.755 --> 00:55:40.424
And I don't let things slide.

00:56:21.006 --> 00:56:22.382
DIVORCE

00:56:22.466 --> 00:56:24.718
PLAINTIFF CHA JEONGHO
DEFENDANT PARK SUJEONG

00:56:33.602 --> 00:56:34.811
I'm sorry.

00:57:35.873 --> 00:57:36.915
Excuse me.

00:57:39.668 --> 00:57:42.546
Juhyeong already left. You should go.

00:58:06.612 --> 00:58:08.155
I crossed the line.

00:58:10.407 --> 00:58:11.825
Why did I do that?

00:59:01.458 --> 00:59:02.584
INMATE NAME: JANG SUGIL

00:59:02.668 --> 00:59:05.170
<i>You think you're here as a lawyer?</i>

00:59:05.254 --> 00:59:06.922
<i>You're a loser keeping me company.</i>

00:59:15.722 --> 00:59:17.724
<i>People like you
are born into nice families</i>

00:59:17.808 --> 00:59:20.102
<i>and go to expensive law schools,</i>

00:59:20.185 --> 00:59:22.646
<i>where it's easier
to become a lawyer.</i>

00:59:23.355 --> 00:59:25.607
<i>How could you even relate
to something like this?</i>

00:59:38.912 --> 00:59:40.122
<i>Are you okay?</i>

00:59:52.634 --> 00:59:56.305
<i>Now, you're not Cha Jeongho's attorney
and just Ahn Juhyeong, right?</i>

01:00:18.660 --> 01:00:25.626
Law and The City

01:00:55.489 --> 01:00:59.201
Law and The City

01:00:59.284 --> 01:01:01.411
<i>I crossed the line. I'm sorry.</i>

01:01:01.495 --> 01:01:03.622
What do you need
that fancy law license for?

01:01:05.290 --> 01:01:06.625
Who are you, Mister?

01:01:06.708 --> 01:01:08.752
<i>We're too young
to be criminally responsible.</i>

01:01:08.836 --> 01:01:11.046
That would make me
too scared to have kids.

01:01:11.505 --> 01:01:14.466
He always brings girls here
to woo them.

01:01:14.550 --> 01:01:15.801
<i>What do you do to woo them?</i>

01:01:16.385 --> 01:01:17.678
<i>But it won't work for Huiji.</i>

01:01:17.761 --> 01:01:19.721
<i>Juhyeong, I'm a busy person too.</i>

01:01:19.805 --> 01:01:22.432
- Attorney Ha Sanggi?
<i>- I bet someone got him that job.</i>

01:01:22.516 --> 01:01:23.892
<i>Having fun playing a commoner?</i>

01:01:24.852 --> 01:01:25.978
<i>Actually…</i>

01:01:27.104 --> 01:01:28.772
<i>Why don't you have a meal with me?</i>

01:01:29.731 --> 01:01:30.816
<i>A promise is a promise.</i>

01:01:39.992 --> 01:01:41.994
Translated by Hye Min Eom